oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Centerville stores
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the north side of a city square in Centerville. People are gathered on the sidewalks outside the buildings. Among the shops are J.D. Flowers' building (with a telegraph exchange upstairs), W.D. & T.S. Thompson's Store, Susie Suggs' Millinery, and a job printing office. Upstairs on the right are the law offices of J.A. Bates & W.V. Flowers.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Commercial streets; Stores & shops
